More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have problems with obesity, with 9 per cent of all pupils and 5 per cent of all children are overweight. 
Recent surveys have shown - obese children usually come from families with unhealthy lifestyles. 
This shows once again how important for the healthy development of a human being is the environment in which he or she and the examples are surrounded. 
The tables are adipöser children sausages were up to 50% more likely on the table than in families in which important children live. 
More than 19 percent of the obese children had on the eve of the education campaign under the slogan "obesity is not a coincidence" chips for dinner. 
In families with sport is not exactly the favorite, but it also affects the majority of today's students, only 15 percent replied that their parents at least once in the week found time for active movement. 
Survey of 900 children 
The survey took place last year at the end of the school year, nearly 900 children from primary schools throughout the Czech Republic. 
This was the second year of action "obesity is not a coincidence," the general health insurance company and the company Unilever will be supported. 
So far, the project is more than 12 thousand pupils from 4th and 8th classes. 
Other unhealthy diet and lack of movement in the family are key factors for the rising number of children with overweight or even obesity are responsible. 
"Only half of the surveyed children, for example, five times a day, the modus zweites frühstück Frühstück-Mittagessen-Vesper-Abendbrot - one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet," is one of the polls. 
No breakfast and sausage for dinner 
Experts point out that even relatively minor matters, such as the regular breakfast time of the family are important for the healthy development of a child. 
In the Czech Republic but only 23 percent of the families of the pupils. 
And, in most families, everyone frühstückt for themselves. 
The worst was the fact that every tenth family is not gefrühstückt at all. 
The breakfast is a cornerstone of a healthy daily diet. 
The survey test, among other things, to the day that the families with obese children much more often unhealthy chips consumed. 
And almost everyone - regardless of weight, drink every day sweet soft drinks (70%) 
Although more than 40 per cent of children surveyed sport, but only less than half of their parents do that - which is only 15 per cent. 
Just do your own menu 
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and girls from 13 schools), offered opportunities for appetite and opinion to compile their own menu. 
"As far as Czech children between 12 and 15 in terms of nutrition, is a far cry from the ideal of a healthy diet. 
Among their favorite speises were many speises meal, meat courts and natural sweeteners. 
"What is alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet soft drinks," will be highlighted in the final report on the survey. 
At lunch, the main court, triumphed pasta just before poultry. 
Pulses, the children almost never liked, and the popularity of fish and vegetables as lunch was very low. 
Hinkehr health 
At the same time, the survey also showed that the children are very willing to change their eating habits, if they get accurate information. 
"In the control group of the survey involved the questionnaire after completion of the educational presentation" obesity is not a coincidence, "filling out, was a significant shift of preferences in many cases to principles of healthy eating," is included in the results of the project. 
This was an example of the sweet Limos, where many children began to give the priority ordinary water. 
The US military in the questionnaire is also much more chicken or fish as a main course of the day and were ready to eat less Knödel or sweet foods. 
