Who is at all? 
Hardly anyone understands what is happening or why this war is being waged at all. 
"There is a lack of facts," Englund says so, "guesswork, assumptions, hopes, fears, fixed ideas, conspiracy theories abound, dreams, aufgemöbelt Alpträumen and rumour." 
"Beauty and horror" follows individuals such as Florence Farmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard, a young German matrosen. 
