The public is increasingly behaving as if their people in uniform suffering. 
"We were not victims," said Brigade General Sean B. MacFarland, who commanded the troops in Iraq and will soon go to Afghanistan. 
"But apparently is the only way of supporting those who are to put ourselves in the unfortunate souls." 
