MSS has announced a research protocol to the discovery of the gene for obesity 
Mexico's Social Security Institution is leading a research project on the discovery of the gene for obesity among children and adolescents, which will be supported by specialists of the IPN. 
The Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social - IMSS (Social Security Institution of Mexico) announced that a research project on the discovery of the gene for obesity among children and young people under the title "genetics of obesity in childhood and youth," with which the genetic markers associated with obesity are to be found. 
Miguel Cruz Lopez, head of the Unidad de Investigación Médica en Bioquímica (department for medical research, focus on biochemistry) at the clinic, Hospital de Especialidades del Centro regions Médico Nacional Siglo XXI stated that a multidisciplinary team, consisting of doctors, pflegern health, nutrition specialists and social workers has been built. 
This team will be supported by specialists and students of the postgraduate studies at the Instituto Nacional de Salud Pública (INSP) and the Italian de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados (Cinvestav) del Instituto Politécnico Nacional (IPN). 
The public is invited to take part in the study, interested parties will be able to IMSS sports venues in the valley of Mexico, where every Saturday from 8am tests will be carried out with children and adolescents. 
He stressed that the investigation on the sports ground of Cuauhtémoc (in the west of the state México) and began since the 8th October at the sports venue of Nezahualcóyolt (in the east of the federal state México) will continue. 
If the goal of 500 to 600 individuals is achieved, the study on the sports ground of Independencia (in the south of the main urban bezirks) continued and Morelos (in the north of the main urban bezirks) concluded. 
